Simply start all three service containers (mongodb, elasticsearch, graylog2) using "docker-compose up"

Default configuration:
----------------------
Graylog web uri:   http://localhost:9000
Graylog user/pass: admin/admin

Logger inputs (TCP ports): 12201 - 12209
Logger inputs (UDP ports): 12211 - 12219

To change Graylog web uri, ports or user/password see docker-compose.yml and for additonal info also Graylog docs at http://docs.graylog.org/en/2.1/pages/installation/manual_setup.html

Alternative:

Create all three containers using the create.sh scripts in the specific service folders and manually start the docker containers.
This will also copy the GeoLite2-City database into the graylog container for GeoIP lookup.
